quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"So, does he not know (that), when whatever is in the tombs is scattered away"
  100,10,And whatever is in the breasts is sought out
  100,11,Surely upon that Day their Lord is indeed of them Ever-Cognizant
  101,1,The Smiter
  101,2,What is the Smiter
  101,3,And what makes you realize what the Smiter is
  101,4,The Day (whereon) mankind will be like disseminated moths
  101,5,And the mountains will be like carded wool tufts
  101,6,"Then, as for him whose scales weigh heavy, (i.e., with good deeds)"
  101,7,So he will be in a satisfied livelihood
  101,8,"And, as for him whose scales weigh light, (i.e., with deeds)"
  101,9,"Then his home is the bottom of Hell (Literally: his mother is tumbling into Hell)"
  101,10,And what makes you realize what it is
  101,11,(It is) a Fire burning hot
  102,1,(Gross) multiplying diverts you
  102,2,Till you visit the cemeteries
  102,3,Not at all! (But) eventually you will know
  102,4,"Again (Literally: Thereafter) not at all! (But) eventually you will know"
  102,5,Not at all! (But) if you know with the knowledge of certitude
  102,6,Indeed you will definitely see Hell-Fire
  102,7,"(Again), (Literally: Thereafter) indeed you will definitely see it with the eye of certitude"
  102,8,Thereafter indeed you will definitely be questioned upon that Day concerning (the worldly) bliss
  103,1,"And (by) the afternoon! (Or: time)"
  103,2,Surely man is indeed in (sheer) loss
  103,3,"Except the ones who have believed, and done deeds of righteousness, and enjoin each other to the Truth, and enjoin each other to patience"
  104,1,"Woe to every persistent slanderer, persistent defamer"
  104,2,Who has gathered wealth and counted it over
  104,3,He reckons that his wealth has made him eternal
  104,4,Not at all! Indeed he will definitely be flung off into the Crusher
  104,5,And what makes you realize what the Crusher is
  104,6,(It is) the Fire of Allah kindled
  104,7,Which views the heart-sights
  104,8,"Surely it is vaulted over (i.e., with no outlet) upon them"
  104,9,In pillars widely extended
  105,1,"Have you not seen how your Lord performed with the companions (i.e., owners) of the elephant"
  105,2,Did He not make their plotting go into great error
  105,3,And He sent upon them baleful birds (in flocks)
  105,4,Throwing against them stones of baked clay
  105,5,So He made them like green blades eaten (up)
  106,1,"For the (customary) accord (Or: joining together) of Quraysh"
  106,2,Their (customary) accord for the winter and summer caravan
  106,3,So let them worship The Lord of this House
  106,4,Who has fed them against hunger and secured them from fear
  107,1,Have you seen him who cries lies to the Doom
  107,2,That is the one who repulses the orphan
  107,3,And does not urge the (offering) of food to the indigent
  107,4,So woe to the ones who pray
  107,5,Who are they that are unmindful of their prayer
  107,6,Who are they that show off
  107,7,And (refuse and) prevent (small) kindnesses
  108,1,Surely We have given you the Abundance
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and slaughter (the sacrifice)
  108,3,"Surely your antagonist is he who is without offspring (Literally: curtailed)"
  109,1,"Say, \"O you disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,Nor are you worshiping what I worship
  109,4,Nor am I worshiping what you have worshiped
  109,5,Nor are you worshiping what I worship
  109,6,"To you is your religion, and to me is my religion"
  110,1,"When comes the victory of Allah, and the Conquest"
  110,2,And you see mankind entering the Religion of Allah in troops
  110,3,"So extol with the praise of your Lord, and ask Him forgiveness; surely He has (always) been Superbly Relenting"
  111,1,"Would the hands of Abu Lahab be cut up, (i.e., perish) and would he be cut up (too)"
  111,2,"In no way did his wealth avail him, neither whatever he earned"
  111,3,"He will roast at a flaming Fire, (Literally: fire comprising flame)"
  111,4,"And his wife, the constant bearer of firewood"
  111,5,Upon her (long) neck she will have a rope of palm-fibers
  112,1,"Say, \"He is Allah, The Only One"
  112,2,"Allah, The Everlasting Sovereign (The Arabic word is sometimes taken to mean all that is mentioned in verses 3 and)"
  112,3,He has not begotten and has not been begotten
  112,4,And to Him none could be co-equal
  113,1,"Say, \"I take refuge with The Lord of the Daybreak, (Literally: the Splitting \"of the day)"
  113,2,From the evil of whatever He has created
  113,3,And from the evil of a dusky night when it overspreads (its gloom)
  113,4,"And from the evil of the women who spit on the knots, (i.e., perform malignant witchcraft)"
  113,5,And from the evil of an envier when he envies
  114,1,"Say, \"I take refuge with The Lord of mankind"
  114,2,The King of mankind
  114,3,The God of mankind
  114,4,From the evil of the constantly slinking whisperer
  114,5,Who whispers in the breasts of mankind
  114,6,Of the jinn (creatures) and mankind